			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">you are running helpbot.php?
<br />

<br />
basically, with php (using Auno's AOChat.php) where ever you call <span style="font-weight: bold">$aoc-&gt;send_tell([who],  [text],  [blob])</span>
<br />

<br />
you will want to invent the BLOB part.   The helpbot.php code comes with a function called <span style="font-weight: bold">MakeTextBlob()</span>
<br />

<br />
so you can do something simple like this:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">$aoc-&gt;send_tell($sender,  chr(17)."click here".chr(18),  MakeTextBlob($reply));</span>
<br />

<br />
the chr(17) is the start of a clickable link, and chr(18) is the end
<br />

<br />

<br />
make sense?<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"> </span></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Beaker on Fri Nov 21, 2003 7:10 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
