			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Beaker wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">yeah, IGNbot is also a nice window based bot, and has everything you want to do, already built in
<br />

<br />
Consider running IGNbot if you can't figure out how to do what you need with helpbot.php
<br />

<br />
Everytime I try to make something window-based on the next version of Helpbot, my wife says "NO!  I hate having to click on everything!" so I have to keep inventing compromises.  hehe</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
IGNbot uses the same syntax for blogs ($aoc&gt;sent_tell...)
<br />

<br />
allthough IGN has an additional packet function called send(): which autoblobs all text and auto-convert dynavars like "(blue)hi there" etc.
<br />

<br />
automatically to same target as it came from(tell/group/guild):
<br />
ex: send($sender,"message","windowtext");
<br />

<br />
to a specifed target:
<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinetext","windowtext","guild");
<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinetext","windowtext","group");
<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinetext","windowtext","tell");
<br />

<br />
invite/kick to/from chatgroup:
<br />

<br />
ex: send("join",$sender,"message");
<br />
ex: send("leave",$sender,"message");
<br />

<br />
or for ex: itemdata:
<br />

<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinetext",Array(ql=&gt;#,lid=&gt;#,hid=&gt;),"tell");
<br />

<br />
or several packets in a row with counter:
<br />

<br />
ex: (will send two tells);
<br />
send($sender,"chatlinetext",Array(1&gt;="hi there,"2=&gt;"hi again"),"tell");
<br />

<br />
can  also do the same with dynavars (the dynavar "(new)" triggers a new tell/split window):
<br />

<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinetext","hi there(new)hi again(new)bye","tell");
<br />

<br />
You can also define that the bot shouldnt autoblob the data, and/or shouldnt autoconvert dynavars,  the send(); function structure is:
<br />

<br />
function send($reciever,$response,$blob = "\0",$target = "",$dynamic = 1, $packit = 1, $splitit = 1){}
<br />

<br />
as you can see, it defaults to autoblob ($packit = 1) and auto dynavar it, and autosplits blobs larger than 7000 characters if the target is a tell, and 4000 characters if the target is a guild/chatgroup, but that can also be turned off.
<br />

<br />
ex: send($sender,"chatlinemsg","windowmsg","tell",0,0,0); &lt; will turn off autoblob, dynavars and autosplitting.
<br />

<br />
Amona<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.monkerud.com/ign156.zip" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Artist previously known as IGN</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
