<br />

<br />
$sender = the targetplayer that gets the message if its a tell, in straight-reply commands this is often the trigger-person, but if the person issuing the command isnt the same as the targer-person then $sender would be meant to be set as the target person, initially $sender is always the trigger-person. 
<br />

<br />
Ex i do:
<br />
/tell botname time
<br />
would make the bot do a:
<br />
$sender="Amona";
<br />
send($sender,"click here for world-times","US:blabla\r\nEurope: blablabl..");
<br />

<br />
Let's say i have an additional parameter in the time command &gt; nickname:
<br />
ex:
<br />
/tell botname time &gt; Fatal
<br />
would make the bot do the same, but something like, (assuming you made a if condition checking for "&gt;" and a nickname):
<br />
$sender="Amona";
<br />
$reciever="Fatal";
<br />
And then maybe:
<br />

<br />
send($sender,"sent the wordtimes to ".$reviever);
<br />
send($reciever,"click here for world-times","US:blabla\r\nEurope: blablabl..");
<br />

<br />

<br />
Assuming this is IGN since you use the send();
<br />
the line would go ex in a plugin you make, example:
<br />
/tell yourbot plugin time
<br />
*bot will open a new file in notepad called time.php with a ready beginners-template which you can edit*
<br />
*edit it and save it, then try /tell yourbot time*
<br />

<br />
ex in the time.php file:
<br />

<br />
&lt;?
<br />
send($sender,"click here for world-times","US:blabla\r\nEurope: blablabl..");
<br />
$reply=""; // clears any text in the often used $reply var in Helpbot based bot's like IGN.
<br />
$noreply=""; //prevents it from using the global send at the end of the loopback since it has allready sent a tell with the first line
<br />
?&gt;
<br />

<br />
Amona<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.monkerud.com/ign156.zip" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Artist previously known as IGN</a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Amona on Fri Nov 21, 2003 11:53 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
