			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">the "windowtext" only works on IGNbot, not on helpbot.php
<br />

<br />
basically you need to know this:
<br />

<br />
when you send a /tell out to someone, there are three parts needed:  
<br />
1: who it's going to
<br />
2. the text of the message
<br />
3. the contents of the popup window
<br />

<br />
so where ever you see in Helpbot's code the following text:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">$aoc-&gt;send_tell</span> you will need to give <span style="font-weight: bold">send_tell</span> those three parts.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Here's the tricky part:  the popup window contents need to be wraped up into a BLOB (<span style="font-weight: bold">b</span>inary <span style="font-weight: bold">l</span>arge <span style="font-weight: bold">ob</span>ject).    That's what the function called <span style="font-weight: bold">MakeTextBlob</span> comes in to play.
<br />

<br />

<br />
so if you have a /tell in helpbot.php that would look like this
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">$aoc-&gt;send_tell($sender, $reply, "\0");</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">"\0"</span> means empty
<br />

<br />
and you want the $reply part to be inside of a popup window, you would need to convert the code to look like this:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$window_contents=MakeTextBlob&#40;$reply&#41;;
<br />
$reply = chr&#40;17&#41;.&quot;click here&quot;.chr&#40;18&#41;;
<br />
$aoc-&gt;send_tell&#40;$sender, $reply, $window_contents&#41;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"> </span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
